title: OBR Volunteers

creator: Operation BBQ Relief
descriptionHtml:
Operation BBQ Relief is a disaster relief 501c3 non-profit that has provided millions of meals to families in need and first responders after disaster strikes. This application is used by the Volunteers of Operation BBQ Relief to register to volunteer, sign up for events, get training through OBR University, get notifications for events and deployments, make and keep track of donations, as well as track certifications that you earn or may already have.

Operation BBQ Relief aids communities and first responders affected by natural disasters by providing the one hot meal that matters during times of need. Operation BBQ Relief with a network of volunteers and equipment across the country can mobilize immediately following natural disasters and be serving hot meals within 24-48 hours of the disaster.

Operation BBQ Relief travels the country year-round always serving those in need – not only during times of crisis. In 2019, we launched The Always Serving Project®, where we help communities across America provide meals to veterans, first responders, frontline health workers, the military community, essential employees, and the homeless in need through educational and event programs.

This application is used by the Volunteers of Operation BBQ Relief to register to volunteer, sign up for events, get training through OBR University, get notifications for events and deployments, make and keep track of donations, as well as track certifications that you earn or may already have.

Operation BBQ Relief aids communities and first responders affected by natural disasters by providing the one hot meal that matters during times of need. Operation BBQ Relief with a network of volunteers and equipment across the country can mobilize immediately following natural disasters and be serving hot meals within 24-48 hours of the disaster.

Operation BBQ Relief travels the country year-round always serving those in need – not only during times of crisis. In 2019, we launched The Always Serving Project®, where we help communities across America provide meals to veterans, first responders, frontline health workers, the military community, essential employees, and the homeless in need through educational and event programs.
